{
  "stem": "8775.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And this was up to about 1940, '41, when we were able to freely travel from one city to the next.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "There was no, no problem.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Actually, the city of Szolnok was a city which was, as I mentioned, 40,000 residents, and it was like a large family.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "The Jewish community was-- consisted of two basic groups, was the conservative group, which we called Neolog, they had their own temple.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And the Orthodox, they had their own temple as well.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And my parents attended services Friday and Saturday, and during the high holy days.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And my father gave generously, pledging for the support of the Chevra Kadisha, and the support of the temple.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Chevra Kadisha is a burial society, which takes care of the burial arrangements for people who don't have the necessary funds to take care of it.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And besides-- as I mentioned to you, besides my uncle who lived there, Miklos, and Mariska, who was my aunt, we also had another family member living in Szolnok.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was my mother's uncle.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "His name was Flamm, F-L-A-M-M.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "His first name was Oscar.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he lived there with his wife, whom he met in Germany.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The lady was German and also a Roman Catholic lady.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They had no child, no children.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] And his mother lived with them, who was very elderly.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she lived with them in one house.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they were the ideal couple.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they were ideal for us, because I had the benefit of both worlds, having Christmas celebrated at their house, and Hanukkah celebrated in our house.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And of course, the language was strictly German.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And talking about the German language, when I-- growing up-- when I have grown up, I had a nanny who came from Austria.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
